# Regression: switching activities MUST wipe the outgoing panel's
# click-rects, or a click at the incoming panel's coord routes to the
# outgoing panel's handler (the "previously viewed screen getting the
# clicks" class user-report 2026-07-15, prior round-11 F1 report).
#
# Repro shape:
#   1. Switch to HTTP  → populates http_panel_filter_input, section
#      headers, `+ New` chips, etc.
#   2. Switch to Notes → Notes panel draws (filter row lands at a
#      similar coord to HTTP's filter row).
#   3. Click at a coord inside the sidebar column that WOULD have
#      matched HTTP's chips before the round-15 systematic clear.
#   4. Assertion: no HTTP-panel prompt / overlay / state change fired.
#      (Whatever HTTP would have popped — "New collection name",
#      "New request", etc. — must be absent.)
#
# The systematic fix in PaneRects::clear_activity_panel_rects (called
# at the top of ui/mod.rs section-dispatch) wipes all 43 activity-
# panel-scoped rects on every frame; only the currently-drawn panel
# repopulates. This test exercises just one switch, but the whole
# class collapses to the same code path — cover-once-cover-all.

write dummy.txt hello
open dummy.txt

# Populate HTTP panel rects.
command view.activity_http
wait 100

# Switch to Notes.
command view.activity_notes
wait 100

# The Notes panel is now visible. Click at a coord in the sidebar
# column (col 10) at a row inside the panel body. Under the old
# behavior this would have hit a stale HTTP rect — under the fix
# it either does nothing or clicks a Notes-owned target.
click 10 5
wait 100

# The screen must NOT contain any HTTP-panel prompt strings that
# would only appear if a stale HTTP click hijacked the event.
expect screen lacks "New collection name"
expect screen lacks "New request"
expect screen lacks "New env"
expect screen lacks "New chain"

# Additionally: the sidebar header must still read "NOTES", not
# "HTTP" — a stale HTTP handler often calls `set_activity_section`
# to swap the sidebar back (which was the round-11 F1 symptom).
expect screen contains "NOTES"
expect screen lacks "COLLECTIONS"
